        "client_msg_id": "7ed61070-908f-4728-8dc3-408d4038142c",
        "text": "Hi everyone! I’m recently working  on *Lain*, a programming language for distributed computation that attempts to implements some idea from smalltalk\/pharo and scheme in propagator model,\nThe core premise is that the compiler itself is a propagator network: it compiles ASTs into meta-compiler networks where the AST can be *partially evaluated* at any point. This allows the environment to remain fluid even in distributed settings. I’ve recently synchronized the repository with *Gun.js*. This allows for a single, universal environment shared across multiple peers,  The prototype is in a very early research stage, and the design is evolving rapidly. I’d love to hear your thoughts! Repo: <https:\/\/github.com\/Semi-0\/lain-lang>",
